The CO2 hydrogenation was performed in a closed stainless-steel chamber under atmospheric pressure. Before fixed at the bottom of the stainless-steel reaction cell, the wafer-based catalysts were thoroughly washed with deionized water. After evacuation, the mixture of CO2 and H2 with various ratios was injected the chamber. The reaction was carried at the setting temperatures. Aft the reaction, the chamber was cool down to room temperature. The gaseous and liquidous products were analyzed by a gas chromatograph (GC-9080, Sun) equipped with a flame ionization detector (FID) detector and a thermal conductivity detector (TCD). Calculation of CO evolution rate, turnover frequency (TOF) and turnover number (TON) based on the following equation.COevolutionrate=COyieldperunitareaofcatalystperhourMassofcatalystperunitarea\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
